SENATE BILL NO. 422
BY SENATOR MILLER
1 AN ACT
2 To amend and reenact R.S. 14:98.4(D) and to enact R.S. 14:98.4(E), relative to driving
3 offenses; to provide relative to penalties for fourth offense operating while impaired;
4 to provide for unsupervised probation in certain circumstances; and to provide for
5 related matters.
6 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
7 Section 1. R.S. 14:98.4(D) is hereby amended and reenacted and R.S. 14:98.4(E) is
8 hereby enacted to read as follows:
9 §98.4. Operating while impaired; fourth offense; penalties
10 * * *
11 D. Except as provided in Paragraph (A)(2) of this Section, in addition to
12 any sentence of imprisonment, home incarceration, treatment program or drug
13 division probation program as provided for by R.S. 13:5301 et seq., supervised
14 probation, or parole, the court shall order that, beginning on the date of the
15 offender's release from incarceration or the offender's completion of home
16 incarceration, a treatment program or drug division probation program,
17 supervised probation, or parole, the offender be placed on unsupervised
18 probation, with the unsupervised probation ending either upon the full term
19 date of the original sentence or twenty years from the date of sentencing,
20 whichever period is longer.
